WEBVTT

00:55.096 --> 00:57.140
- What do you feel like eating?
- Something good.

00:57.265 --> 01:00.018
- Something good? Korean food?
- You have to do it.

01:00.226 --> 01:01.811
- Korean food would be good.
- Sounds good.

01:01.895 --> 01:03.563
- Japanese food?
- I like everything.

01:03.646 --> 01:05.273
- Really? Lamb skewers too?
- Go slow.

01:05.356 --> 01:06.649
- Set a screen.
- No.

01:09.694 --> 01:12.822
- Let's go.
- Go for it.

01:13.615 --> 01:16.242
EPISODE 2

01:22.957 --> 01:23.958
Concentrate everyone!

01:24.876 --> 01:27.295
Has he changed?

01:27.378 --> 01:28.546
Or did I just not know?

01:28.963 --> 01:30.465
Your boyfriend can be pretty assertive.

01:32.133 --> 01:33.218
In what aspect?

01:33.927 --> 01:35.386
The way he talks

01:36.346 --> 01:38.848
and his overall vibe.
Has he always been like that?

01:40.725 --> 01:43.686
He tries not to show it,
but he does have a strong sense of pride.

02:18.513 --> 02:19.556
Are you okay?

02:19.639 --> 02:22.058
Don't worry. That's not your boyfriend.

02:24.978 --> 02:26.604
- Oh, you're right.
- I find him attractive.

02:28.565 --> 02:30.942
Are you this smitten by Gi-seok
after that short chat?

02:31.025 --> 02:33.361
Not Gi-seok.
I'm talking about that guy who fell.

02:35.446 --> 02:36.865
I keep noticing him.

02:37.448 --> 02:38.491
Isn't he attractive?

02:40.076 --> 02:41.870
Well, I haven't gotten a good look at him.

02:42.412 --> 02:43.830
There's no need. He just stands out.

02:45.165 --> 02:46.291
Shall I hit on him?

02:46.916 --> 02:48.084
I told you to behave yourself.

02:48.751 --> 02:50.170
I haven't even done anything.

02:52.463 --> 02:55.133
Be on your good behavior
so that you don't embarrass Gi-seok.

03:00.722 --> 03:01.806
Hey, are you all right?

03:02.515 --> 03:04.809
- Yes, I'm fine.
- My gosh, I'm sorry.

03:06.311 --> 03:07.395
Can you play?

03:07.812 --> 03:09.522
I have to. To win, that is.

03:23.786 --> 03:25.788
Where should we go?
What do you want to eat?

03:26.414 --> 03:29.542
I want to eat so many things, but someone
keeps hinting that I shouldn't say so.

03:31.669 --> 03:33.546
You don't seem like the type
to be intimidated.

03:35.048 --> 03:37.425
I'll go wash up quickly.
Decide what you two want to eat.

03:37.675 --> 03:38.676
Okay.

03:39.177 --> 03:40.261
- I'm excited.
- Gi-seok.

03:40.428 --> 03:41.930
The team wants to go for grilled pork.

03:42.013 --> 03:43.848
- I have to--
- We'll join you guys.

03:43.932 --> 03:45.183
- What's with you?
- What?

03:45.683 --> 03:47.310
You're more than welcome to join us.

03:48.311 --> 03:49.729
Oh, would you not like the idea?

03:51.397 --> 03:52.649
What are you saying?

03:53.483 --> 03:54.400
So? Shall we join them?

03:55.944 --> 03:57.403
They'll be uncomfortable if we come.

03:57.487 --> 03:59.155
Go with them. We'll figure something out.

03:59.239 --> 04:01.699
Gosh, not at all.
We'd really love to have you two join us.

04:02.992 --> 04:04.077
Hey, Ji-ho.

04:04.827 --> 04:06.246
- Let's go eat.
- What?

04:07.121 --> 04:09.332
Sorry about earlier. Is your foot okay?

04:10.166 --> 04:12.126
Yes, it's fine. Don't worry about it.

04:12.210 --> 04:13.419
God, I feel so bad.

04:15.088 --> 04:17.840
Oh, right. Hey, that thing
I told you about the other day.

04:17.924 --> 04:19.300
- What?
- Remember? That thing.

04:19.592 --> 04:21.886
- Get going first. We'll meet you there.
- All right.

04:23.388 --> 04:26.516
Then... Wait for me in the car.

04:27.016 --> 04:28.184
- Okay.
- I'll unlock the doors.

04:28.685 --> 04:30.311
- What's this about?
- Jeez.

04:32.355 --> 04:33.606
Are you a teenage boy or what?

04:34.107 --> 04:35.858
Don't be so sheepish.

04:36.985 --> 04:38.903
You said you'll start dating again,
didn't you?

04:39.570 --> 04:43.449
Then you have to get used
to mingling with people first.

04:44.450 --> 04:45.618
I didn't say I wasn't going.

04:48.246 --> 04:50.957
Hey, Ji-ho.
You're acting so weird these days.

05:30.580 --> 05:32.874
I thought Si-hoon would be home too.

05:34.208 --> 05:35.460
He's busy, you know.

05:37.462 --> 05:39.130
Was Dad okay after we left?

05:40.423 --> 05:41.674
Don't even get me started.

05:42.300 --> 05:45.053
He seemed awfully angry and upset.

05:45.553 --> 05:47.472
So I pretended I didn't notice it
and left him be.

05:48.473 --> 05:51.517
I made these braised short ribs just now,
so it's still warm.

05:51.601 --> 05:53.519
I'm not hungry now. I'll eat it later.

05:55.271 --> 05:57.899
Do you have some kind of health problem?

05:58.232 --> 05:59.484
No, I told you that I'm fine.

06:00.318 --> 06:02.028
You didn't need to get
this herbal medicine.

06:02.195 --> 06:06.240
Oh, right. You should take one now.

06:06.616 --> 06:08.618
You seemed to have no energy at all,
so I--

06:08.701 --> 06:10.244
Okay, I'll make sure I take them.

06:10.745 --> 06:11.954
Do you want a cup of coffee?

06:13.331 --> 06:14.373
Have a seat.

06:17.543 --> 06:19.087
Whenever you act like this,

06:19.629 --> 06:21.964
I feel like I shouldn't let
Jeong-in and Jae-in get married.

06:23.424 --> 06:26.594
You were never the affectionate type,
but you used to tell me stuff.

06:27.011 --> 06:28.930
Since you got married,
you've changed so much.

06:32.141 --> 06:33.810
I'll go back to how I used to be.

06:34.727 --> 06:36.270
It's easier said than done.

06:55.456 --> 06:56.582
About Jeong-in...

06:57.542 --> 06:58.709
Don't let her get married.

07:00.294 --> 07:02.839
- For the rest of her life?
- Why not?

07:03.589 --> 07:05.591
Do you also think
that getting married is a must?

07:07.885 --> 07:10.555
I've been living with your dad
for the past 37 years.

07:11.597 --> 07:13.558
I'm old fashioned like him too, you know.

07:15.017 --> 07:18.479
I think it's better
than never getting married.

07:20.481 --> 07:23.234
Why? Did Jeong-in complain a lot to you?

07:23.317 --> 07:24.569
No, it's just what I think.

07:25.361 --> 07:26.904
She's not like me.

07:27.196 --> 07:28.823
She and Dad will clash a lot.

07:29.991 --> 07:32.535
And you'll be so stressed out
stuck between the two of them.

07:34.704 --> 07:36.289
You've had it the hardest.

07:38.374 --> 07:42.003
You've had to put up with all sorts
of things and be a model for your sisters.

07:42.795 --> 07:44.380
You never had your way.

07:45.715 --> 07:47.008
Even with your marriage--

07:47.300 --> 07:48.843
Take care of Jeong-in instead.

07:51.762 --> 07:53.222
She doesn't listen to me, you know.

07:54.265 --> 07:56.225
She's very opinionated.

07:57.477 --> 07:58.811
She sure is a special one.

07:59.812 --> 08:01.314
At least one of us is outspoken.

08:02.190 --> 08:03.316
That's true.

08:13.951 --> 08:15.745
Can I say a few words?

08:17.580 --> 08:22.126
Thank you all for inviting me.
I had such a great time.

08:22.210 --> 08:24.837
I know that you guys
are all younger than me,

08:24.921 --> 08:28.841
but I'll do my best as an older member.

08:29.550 --> 08:31.177
I'll do my very best.

08:31.260 --> 08:32.386
Thank you everyone!

08:32.762 --> 08:34.096
- Thank you!
- Welcome!

08:34.180 --> 08:35.848
- Okay!
- Let's celebrate.

08:35.932 --> 08:37.183
Everyone, well done.

08:37.266 --> 08:39.101
- You did a good job too.
- Drink up.

08:39.185 --> 08:40.061
I had fun playing.

08:48.903 --> 08:49.987
Did I do well today?

08:54.742 --> 08:56.619
I think you need a lot of practice.

08:57.995 --> 08:59.121
Mind your own business.

08:59.205 --> 09:02.208
Dude, I'm serious.
You need special training.

09:02.542 --> 09:04.252
- You keep...
- I'm not really good at...

09:04.335 --> 09:05.753
Why only me?

09:07.088 --> 09:09.966
- Half an hour a day, starting tomorrow.
- Half an hour?

09:22.019 --> 09:23.980
You need to eat a lot to be strong.

09:25.523 --> 09:28.401
Exactly, you know very well.
Then why did you eat so little?

09:31.028 --> 09:32.071
At the kindergarten?

09:37.702 --> 09:38.911
Someone's inside.

09:41.956 --> 09:42.915
What did you say, Eun-u?

09:43.499 --> 09:45.209
Daddy couldn't hear you. Say it again.

09:49.714 --> 09:50.965
Today, I can't.

09:51.716 --> 09:53.009
I'll come see you in three days.

09:56.762 --> 09:58.389
Okay. In two days, then.

10:00.933 --> 10:02.018
Did I drink?

10:05.354 --> 10:06.439
No, I didn't.

10:09.275 --> 10:10.318
I really didn't.

10:19.285 --> 10:20.369
I'm not lying.

10:23.497 --> 10:24.749
I can't even have just a glass?

10:28.753 --> 10:29.837
All right.

10:41.057 --> 10:42.391
Why are you still here?

10:43.142 --> 10:44.852
I just got off the phone.

10:54.487 --> 10:56.072
Is your kid's name Eun-u?

10:58.991 --> 11:00.076
I overheard it earlier.

11:03.537 --> 11:04.789
I must say, you're a good liar.

11:06.248 --> 11:07.541
You did drink.

11:08.668 --> 11:11.128
He doesn't like it when I drink.
That's why I keep...

11:13.589 --> 11:15.383
I really hate lying.

11:20.721 --> 11:21.889
Go in first.

11:21.972 --> 11:24.100
If we go back in together,
we'll have to lie.

11:26.227 --> 11:28.479
Well, we just used the washroom.

11:31.399 --> 11:33.067
All right, then. Do as you please.

11:48.082 --> 11:50.042
- Maybe I shouldn't have come.
- You're welcome.

11:50.626 --> 11:51.460
Eat up.

11:52.336 --> 11:54.463
- There's more meat.
- Goodbye!

11:56.882 --> 11:59.385
Yes, I had some. Eat up.

11:59.468 --> 12:01.929
- What are you doing here?
- Oh, this guy called me.

12:02.471 --> 12:05.891
I called this starving future civil
servant so that he can have some meat.

12:06.142 --> 12:07.143
I'm glad you called him.

12:07.226 --> 12:10.020
- I hope it's okay that I came.
- Gosh, don't worry.

12:10.104 --> 12:11.772
Don't you worry. I tagged along too.

12:12.148 --> 12:14.150
- Should we do a toast?
- Cheers.

12:14.233 --> 12:16.235
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

12:16.318 --> 12:19.655
- It's nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you. Welcome.

12:24.285 --> 12:26.412
- You plan to take the civil service exam.
- That's right.

12:28.622 --> 12:29.790
And that guy...

12:32.084 --> 12:36.589
You mean, this guy? I told you earlier
that I work with Gi-seok.

12:36.922 --> 12:38.340
- Oh, that's right.
- Oh, did you?

12:38.424 --> 12:40.759
So, you work at a bank.
You touch money for a living.

12:40.843 --> 12:42.887
- You shouldn't drink anymore.
- Why shouldn't I?

12:43.888 --> 12:45.181
And you? What do you do?

12:46.056 --> 12:47.933
Oh, I'm--

12:48.017 --> 12:49.977
Quiz time. Here's a quiz for you.

12:51.312 --> 12:52.521
What do you think his job is?

12:53.105 --> 12:54.940
Everyone, be quiet. Don't say anything.

12:55.357 --> 12:56.317
Take a guess.

12:56.400 --> 12:58.652
She won't be able to guess it.
I mean, how would she know?

12:58.736 --> 13:00.362
He must have an unusual job.

13:01.739 --> 13:04.033
- What do you think it is?
- What could it be?

13:04.783 --> 13:06.285
Jeong-in, what do you think it is?

13:07.953 --> 13:09.288
How would I know?

13:09.663 --> 13:10.748
Gosh.

13:12.374 --> 13:13.542
- Can I get a hint?
- A hint?

13:17.046 --> 13:18.380
A quack.

13:18.756 --> 13:20.257
- Something is stuck here.
- Are you okay?

13:20.758 --> 13:22.885
- A doctor, right?
- It's similar.

13:22.968 --> 13:24.428
What's similar to a doctor?

13:24.512 --> 13:25.846
- Think about what they wear.
- What?

13:25.930 --> 13:26.889
The coat.

13:28.098 --> 13:28.933
The coat?

13:29.475 --> 13:31.227
What? So, you knew!

13:32.561 --> 13:33.395
Right?

13:33.479 --> 13:35.898
- I think I overheard it earlier.
- I knew it.

13:35.981 --> 13:38.859
Yes, I mentioned earlier
that I'm a pharmacist.

13:38.943 --> 13:40.402
- Jeez.
- Hey, you ruined the fun.

13:40.486 --> 13:41.820
No wonder she seemed sharp-witted.

13:42.780 --> 13:44.365
You're a pharmacist.

13:45.032 --> 13:46.242
I never would've guessed.

13:46.450 --> 13:48.118
- Really?
- Yes.

13:48.202 --> 13:50.955
- By the way...
- Go ahead.

13:52.289 --> 13:54.291
I've been wanting to say this
since earlier.

13:55.834 --> 13:57.753
Both sisters are gorgeous.

13:57.836 --> 13:59.255
- Totally.
- You've just noticed that?

14:00.089 --> 14:02.550
There are three girls in our family,

14:03.050 --> 14:04.468
and I'm the prettiest one.

14:06.387 --> 14:08.055
I think Jeong-in is the prettiest one.

14:09.723 --> 14:10.933
Jeez, come on.

14:11.016 --> 14:13.060
- All right. Do you guys agree?
- My glass is empty.

14:13.143 --> 14:14.436
Those of you who agree, cheers.

14:14.520 --> 14:16.689
- I agree. Cheers.
- I don't agree.

14:17.314 --> 14:18.524
Gosh, Gi-seok.

14:32.955 --> 14:34.123
Do we have any fruit?

14:55.561 --> 14:57.313
By the way, why have you been doing that?

14:58.814 --> 15:00.190
To me, this is like meditation.

15:01.317 --> 15:03.068
Why do you even need to meditate?

15:04.528 --> 15:06.071
Who do you think is to blame?

15:07.031 --> 15:10.075
Stop being so overbearing
toward the girls. They're all adults now.

15:10.618 --> 15:12.244
But not real, functioning adults yet.

15:12.995 --> 15:16.081
They're running riot
because you coddle them so much.

15:16.624 --> 15:18.167
How dare they talk back to their father?

15:19.335 --> 15:20.586
Forget it.

15:21.086 --> 15:22.880
I shouldn't have brought it up.

15:23.547 --> 15:25.257
When Jae-in comes back after graduating,

15:25.341 --> 15:26.884
I'm going to marry her off right away.

15:27.259 --> 15:29.094
We're having a hard time
even with Jeong-in.

15:29.720 --> 15:30.846
What are you saying--

15:30.930 --> 15:32.973
Let's give it some thought
before we decide.

15:33.098 --> 15:35.684
That's what Jeong-in wants too.

15:36.018 --> 15:37.603
What does she even know?

15:38.270 --> 15:40.481
Working for a few years
doesn't teach you everything.

15:41.398 --> 15:43.067
And instead of wasting time on this,

15:43.150 --> 15:45.444
you should study how the world works.

15:46.987 --> 15:48.238
You study all you want.

15:48.948 --> 15:52.242
Mr. Principal, go ahead and study
all you want about the world.

15:52.993 --> 15:54.036
Hey!

15:56.163 --> 15:59.208
Is "Hey" my name? Even dogs have names.

16:00.292 --> 16:01.627
Jeez, what's with you today?

16:02.211 --> 16:04.672
If you do that one more time,
I won't let it slide...

16:07.758 --> 16:08.884
You're pathetic.

16:14.723 --> 16:15.557
What the...

16:33.200 --> 16:34.868
"SOMEDAY"

16:39.164 --> 16:40.290
What's going on?

16:41.542 --> 16:44.420
- Did you two reserve the same song?
- Yes, it looks like they did.

16:45.295 --> 16:47.548
- Just sing it together, then.
- Sing it together.

16:47.673 --> 16:48.924
Sing it with her.

16:51.176 --> 16:52.469
Excuse me for a moment.

16:53.220 --> 16:54.430
Oh, okay.

16:56.515 --> 16:57.433
Hello?

17:50.235 --> 17:51.612
I should stop there.

17:52.112 --> 17:53.363
- Why turn it off?
- It was good.

17:53.697 --> 17:54.907
Just because.

17:58.160 --> 17:59.203
Hey.

18:00.662 --> 18:02.790
Is something going on?

18:03.957 --> 18:06.126
With Ji-ho? He had to leave
because of a family matter.

18:08.712 --> 18:10.881
- Is it something bad?
- No, it's nothing serious.

18:11.715 --> 18:13.092
Which song should I sing?

18:13.759 --> 18:15.260
Why did you stop the song?

18:16.053 --> 18:17.096
I just wanted to.

18:18.347 --> 18:19.515
Why aren't you singing?

18:21.266 --> 18:23.018
- Me? I was going to.
- Yes.

18:23.769 --> 18:28.482
Then while you're making your choice,
let's hear from our special guest singer,

18:29.942 --> 18:31.485
- our future civil servant.
- Gosh.

18:32.444 --> 18:33.946
He actually wanted to be a singer,

18:35.239 --> 18:37.157
but he had to give up
because of his looks.

18:38.575 --> 18:39.827
Can he sing that well?

18:40.577 --> 18:43.205
- He's an amazing singer.
- Check out the melody, guys.

18:43.872 --> 18:46.583
- Oh, I love this song!
- Prepare to be amazed.

19:16.238 --> 19:18.240
I'm sorry,
but could you drive a little faster?

19:18.323 --> 19:19.700
- Sure.
- I apologize.

19:44.975 --> 19:49.396
EMERGENCY ROOM

19:49.479 --> 19:53.817
PEDIATRICS

19:57.738 --> 19:59.573
- Oh, you're here.
- How is he?

20:01.200 --> 20:03.994
- What did the doctor say?
- They think it's gastroenteritis.

20:04.953 --> 20:07.539
They said we have to wait
for the full test results.

20:10.667 --> 20:11.919
I had no idea that he was sick.

20:13.378 --> 20:15.547
I feel so bad
that I scolded him for not eating.

20:16.048 --> 20:17.174
It's okay.

20:17.883 --> 20:19.676
You said getting sick
is part of growing up.

20:30.854 --> 20:32.564
Your mom shouldn't have called you.

20:34.358 --> 20:35.984
I should know. It's about my kid.

20:37.945 --> 20:39.821
Don't give Mom a hard time about it.

20:41.281 --> 20:42.783
What about dinner? Have you eaten yet?

20:43.617 --> 20:44.660
Yes.

20:45.661 --> 20:48.121
- Go home. I can stay.
- Don't worry.

20:48.789 --> 20:51.458
What if the two of you get sick too?
Just go home, please.

20:51.875 --> 20:53.502
But you have to go to work tomorrow.

20:53.585 --> 20:54.795
I'll deal with it.

20:56.338 --> 20:57.673
Get going already.

21:30.080 --> 21:31.123
Daddy's here.

21:31.623 --> 21:33.292
Has it been two days already?

21:33.875 --> 21:34.793
No.

21:35.502 --> 21:37.337
I came sooner because I missed you.

21:38.547 --> 21:39.548
Does it still hurt a lot?

21:43.218 --> 21:44.845
When you feel pain, don't hide it.

21:45.762 --> 21:47.306
You have to tell us.

21:47.889 --> 21:51.184
I feel better now that you're here.

21:52.769 --> 21:54.813
I'll be right by your side at all times
from now on.

21:56.565 --> 21:59.526
I'll stay right next to you
so that you never get sick again.

22:02.362 --> 22:03.447
I promise.

22:17.169 --> 22:18.295
Wash up quickly.

22:20.797 --> 22:22.049
Should I send you back to Mom's?

22:24.051 --> 22:25.093
Okay, fine.

22:26.136 --> 22:27.346
And tidy up the table.

22:32.768 --> 22:33.977
By the way, why are you angry?

22:34.770 --> 22:35.937
What are you talking about?

22:36.688 --> 22:39.941
You suddenly got all quiet
at the karaoke bar and you're cranky now.

22:40.817 --> 22:41.860
No, I'm not.

22:46.198 --> 22:47.199
What?

22:47.991 --> 22:49.076
You are cranky.

22:54.039 --> 22:55.123
What's with her?

23:24.861 --> 23:26.029
Are you in bed already?

23:28.240 --> 23:30.826
Nothing's up. I just got out of the shower
and called you.

23:33.662 --> 23:34.830
You must be tired.

23:43.130 --> 23:44.131
Hello.

23:44.631 --> 23:48.385
My gosh, I rarely see you even though
we work at the same broadcasting station.

23:48.718 --> 23:50.762
I know.
Everything is well with you, right?

23:50.846 --> 23:52.639
Well, I'm making ends meet.

23:53.640 --> 23:55.433
Come in for a minute.
Your husband is here.

23:56.726 --> 23:57.978
No, it's okay.

23:58.270 --> 24:00.689
Give him some moral support.
The news isn't until later, right?

24:02.649 --> 24:03.692
Come on.

24:10.657 --> 24:12.159
Your wife is here.

24:12.409 --> 24:13.243
Pardon?

24:15.287 --> 24:18.039
She didn't want to come in
because she was shy, but I insisted.

24:20.709 --> 24:22.836
You're like two peas in a pod.
You're both so shy.

24:23.545 --> 24:24.921
Give each other moral support.

24:26.173 --> 24:27.215
Hey, it's good to see you.

24:29.301 --> 24:30.302
I hope the show goes well.

24:30.385 --> 24:33.305
I have to do a good job.
I can't embarrass you, you know.

24:35.098 --> 24:38.226
Please take good care of her.
I haven't been that attentive lately,

24:38.310 --> 24:39.644
so she's a little mad at me.

24:39.978 --> 24:42.647
I knew it. I wondered
why she seemed sulky for a moment.

24:43.273 --> 24:46.484
Be good to her. You'll pay dearly
if you neglect a wife like her.

24:47.652 --> 24:49.821
What can I do to be a better husband?

24:49.905 --> 24:51.656
I'll make it up to you.

24:53.074 --> 24:54.201
Will that work?

24:55.702 --> 24:58.079
What time do you think we'll be done?

24:59.706 --> 25:01.166
- Today's show is simple.
- Right.

25:01.249 --> 25:02.709
- So we'll be done early?
- Yes.

25:02.959 --> 25:04.544
- See you later, Seo-in.
- See you.

25:15.847 --> 25:16.806
Hey.

25:19.684 --> 25:22.479
I have to talk to you about something.
Wait for me at home.

25:24.940 --> 25:26.942
What? Shall we meet somewhere outside?

25:27.025 --> 25:28.860
It'd be better actually.
Where would be good?

25:42.749 --> 25:44.417
When I got this job,

25:44.501 --> 25:48.004
I thought librarians just sit gracefully
and read books all day long.

25:48.797 --> 25:51.591
But look at this. Why must we
go through these event posters?

25:52.717 --> 25:54.803
Why do they all look the same to me?

25:55.512 --> 25:56.513
That's what I'm saying.

25:59.975 --> 26:02.978
My gosh. Hey, we haven't even finished
going through these.

26:03.728 --> 26:05.188
There's even more.

26:05.981 --> 26:09.192
Let's stop researching blindly like this
and brainstorm again for the concept.

26:09.484 --> 26:12.195
It's our regular book review event,
so we don't find it exciting.

26:13.530 --> 26:16.283
Should we focus on the latest trends?

26:16.366 --> 26:18.660
Jeez, I know nothing
about the latest trends.

26:18.743 --> 26:20.787
I guess I'll have to surf the Internet
all night.

26:32.465 --> 26:33.300
How about seasons?

26:36.177 --> 26:38.471
- I like that.
- I know that winter is over,

26:39.764 --> 26:41.433
but "snow" would've been a nice theme.

26:42.684 --> 26:43.685
Like the first snow?

26:45.312 --> 26:46.313
The last snow.

26:46.396 --> 26:48.898
My gosh, that's a refreshing idea.
"The last snow."

26:49.316 --> 26:50.734
- I haven't heard that before.
- Yes.

26:53.320 --> 26:56.614
Jeong-in, I keep seeing
a whole new side of you these days.

26:57.198 --> 26:58.116
You know?

26:58.575 --> 27:00.660
The other day, you sounded like
a hopeless romantic

27:00.744 --> 27:02.996
and today you're all sentimental.

27:03.913 --> 27:05.749
This is how I really am. Satisfied?

27:07.834 --> 27:08.877
Gosh, hey.

27:09.336 --> 27:11.629
My brain isn't working
because I haven't eaten anything.

27:11.713 --> 27:12.672
Let's go eat something.

27:12.756 --> 27:14.174
- Great idea.
- I know.

27:14.591 --> 27:15.633
- Shall we?
- Yes.

27:18.887 --> 27:20.055
- My gosh.
- Let's go.

27:20.555 --> 27:25.018
MUSIC, TRENDS, SEASONS, SNOW
THE NEXT TIME IT SNOWS

27:28.021 --> 27:29.105
How cute!

27:30.190 --> 27:32.359
- How old are you?
- I'm five.

27:33.068 --> 27:34.194
You're five years old?

27:35.070 --> 27:36.446
You're so adorable.

27:37.781 --> 27:40.283
- Have a good day. Bye.
- Bye!

27:40.533 --> 27:41.993
- Say, "Bye."
- Bye.

27:42.077 --> 27:42.994
Goodbye.

27:45.455 --> 27:46.498
She's so cute.

27:50.210 --> 27:51.252
What's the matter?

27:51.795 --> 27:53.797
What? Nothing. Let's go.

27:55.590 --> 27:57.175
There's nothing I fear more than kids.

27:57.926 --> 27:58.968
Why?

27:59.135 --> 28:01.888
They're so innocent and pure.

28:02.055 --> 28:03.264
What if I hurt them?

28:05.016 --> 28:06.226
Hey, do you ever think that?

28:07.268 --> 28:09.521
Well, I don't know. Maybe.

28:15.902 --> 28:18.113
- What about Eun-u?
- I made sure he's asleep.

28:20.657 --> 28:23.034
I made all this food for you
because you always eat out.

28:23.118 --> 28:24.411
Why are you eating like a bird?

28:24.994 --> 28:26.162
I'm eating, Mom.

28:28.873 --> 28:30.458
Is it okay that you missed work today?

28:30.917 --> 28:32.043
I've told my co-workers.

28:33.294 --> 28:35.547
Eun-u needs to stay here
for another day or two,

28:35.630 --> 28:37.298
so I'll stay here with him. Okay?

28:37.465 --> 28:38.633
Finish your food, go home,

28:38.716 --> 28:40.552
and go back to work tomorrow.

28:40.635 --> 28:42.178
No, I can take a few days off.

28:42.971 --> 28:44.681
Gosh, you shouldn't miss work.

28:45.348 --> 28:47.183
It's not like you have no other option.

28:47.267 --> 28:49.185
Why inconvenience your co-workers?

28:49.436 --> 28:50.478
Don't do that.

28:53.606 --> 28:54.649
Mom.

28:56.985 --> 28:58.194
Shall I move back in?

29:00.613 --> 29:03.199
Living far from work
won't improve the situation at all.

29:03.867 --> 29:06.870
Do you think you'll actually get to see
Eun-u more in the morning and night?

29:07.620 --> 29:08.663
Forget it.

29:11.374 --> 29:13.126
I'm more worried about you.

29:13.835 --> 29:15.086
You're still so young.

29:16.796 --> 29:19.632
Being young is great. I still have
many opportunities ahead.

29:24.471 --> 29:26.723
Do you date at all?

29:29.893 --> 29:31.102
Occasionally.

29:32.479 --> 29:34.189
Have you met anyone that you like?

29:36.316 --> 29:37.358
No, not yet.

29:40.570 --> 29:42.363
Your soul mate will come find you.

29:45.617 --> 29:47.410
- You think so?
- Yes, of course.

29:47.869 --> 29:49.370
Nothing can stop your destiny.

29:50.330 --> 29:52.916
And she'd better come find you.
Will you be single forever?

29:55.001 --> 29:57.128
Gosh, you're obviously not even worried.

30:04.385 --> 30:05.470
Thank you.

30:20.151 --> 30:21.402
Even this one can't make it.

30:22.445 --> 30:23.613
What's happening this week?

30:24.364 --> 30:26.491
- Someone else can't make it?
- Ji-ho can't come.

30:27.575 --> 30:28.827
We might not have enough people.

30:30.537 --> 30:34.249
He left early that day saying
something came up. Is it because of that?

30:35.333 --> 30:36.709
Yes, I think so.

30:38.211 --> 30:39.295
What happened?

30:43.091 --> 30:44.676
- This is top secret.
- Okay.

30:46.344 --> 30:48.638
Actually, he has a kid.

30:50.139 --> 30:52.058
- Oh, he's married?
- No.

30:53.226 --> 30:56.020
He had a girlfriend back in college
and she was quite young.

30:56.855 --> 30:57.981
About 24 at the time?

30:58.356 --> 31:00.233
- Ji-ho was 28 or 29 back then.
- I see.

31:00.775 --> 31:04.153
She hid the fact that she was pregnant
and fell off the face of the earth.

31:04.737 --> 31:06.447
Then she showed up after eight months.

31:07.240 --> 31:08.491
- Out of the blue?
- Yes.

31:09.701 --> 31:11.953
They talked about getting married

31:12.036 --> 31:13.872
and maybe doing it after she gives birth.

31:14.497 --> 31:16.332
She lived with his family
for a little while,

31:17.542 --> 31:19.127
but she vanished again one day.

31:19.210 --> 31:21.421
So, what happened?
Did he not look for her?

31:21.921 --> 31:23.590
When that happened, Ji-ho totally lost it.

31:24.716 --> 31:27.927
He even took a leave of absence
and went everywhere looking for her,

31:28.344 --> 31:29.387
but he couldn't find her.

31:30.430 --> 31:33.224
Later, he found out
that she had already left the country.

31:35.268 --> 31:37.020
My goodness.

31:38.813 --> 31:41.149
- That's crazy.
- Yes.

31:42.358 --> 31:44.527
Jeez, it must have been so hard for him.

31:45.236 --> 31:47.447
A lot of time has passed,
so he's okay now.

31:48.615 --> 31:49.657
But back then...

31:51.075 --> 31:52.201
He was utterly distraught.

31:54.329 --> 31:56.623
Oh, dear. I feel bad for him.

31:58.458 --> 32:00.335
If I had known,
I would've been nicer to him.

32:00.418 --> 32:02.795
- Why? What do you mean?
- What?

32:03.922 --> 32:05.048
I just feel bad for him.

32:06.758 --> 32:09.135
Don't feel bad.
Who cares if he's a single dad?

32:09.928 --> 32:11.512
He makes good money, and he's healthy.

32:12.013 --> 32:13.348
Also, he has wonderful parents.

32:13.932 --> 32:15.058
Everything else is fine.

32:16.142 --> 32:17.226
How is that fine?

32:18.269 --> 32:19.312
What woman would like that?

32:24.150 --> 32:25.401
- Get home safely.
- Bye.

32:47.006 --> 32:49.050
MISO PHARMACY

33:13.157 --> 33:15.076
WOORI PHARMACY

33:34.929 --> 33:35.930
Here you go.

33:39.183 --> 33:40.184
Thank you.

34:43.831 --> 34:44.957
Thank you.

34:48.753 --> 34:49.754
What are you doing here?

34:49.837 --> 34:52.465
I'm just stopping by.
I'll be here tomorrow.

34:52.799 --> 34:54.759
I said it's okay. Don't kill yourself.

34:55.176 --> 34:56.928
It's fine. I can work.

34:57.970 --> 34:59.806
What did the doctor say? Is he okay now?

35:01.474 --> 35:03.559
- Yes, he's fine now.
- Thank goodness.

35:04.769 --> 35:06.938
We just brewed persimmon leaf tea.
Do you want some?

35:07.188 --> 35:09.816
No, thanks. I'll be off. Take it easy.

35:10.149 --> 35:12.318
- Get home safely.
- You can come in late tomorrow morning.

35:17.031 --> 35:18.324
Can I help you find something?

35:19.575 --> 35:21.077
Sorry? It's okay. I'm getting this.

35:24.163 --> 35:25.081
Here.

35:27.250 --> 35:28.751
- Your total is 2,000 won.
- Okay.

35:31.045 --> 35:32.088
Here you go.

35:32.547 --> 35:33.464
Thank you.

35:39.387 --> 35:40.721
I'll wait for you at the corner.

35:44.517 --> 35:46.394
- Here's your 8,000 won.
- Thank you.

35:48.354 --> 35:49.188
- Bye.
- Bye.

35:59.574 --> 36:00.741
Did you come here to see me?

36:02.994 --> 36:05.121
Why would I come all the way here
just to buy this?

36:08.040 --> 36:09.083
What's up?

36:10.960 --> 36:12.545
What's up with you?

36:15.882 --> 36:18.885
They're closing soon, so they'll be out
any minute. Let's go somewhere else.

36:20.219 --> 36:22.096
Can't we just talk here?

36:23.472 --> 36:26.100
If they see us together,
they'll start talking about you.

36:55.671 --> 36:58.382
My son was a little sick.

36:59.383 --> 37:00.843
How? Is it something serious?

37:03.804 --> 37:05.431
He'll be fine in a few days.

37:07.225 --> 37:08.267
That's good news.

37:12.063 --> 37:14.106
I was worried after you left so abruptly.

37:16.567 --> 37:20.321
It seemed serious judging by
how your friends kept their mouths shut.

37:22.198 --> 37:23.699
I was going to forget about it,

37:26.077 --> 37:27.203
but here I am.

37:28.537 --> 37:29.789
You could've just texted.

37:31.415 --> 37:32.875
But you rarely respond.

37:37.129 --> 37:38.673
I did that on purpose,

37:39.048 --> 37:40.675
and I already told you why I did that.

37:47.932 --> 37:48.975
Well,

37:50.309 --> 37:52.019
I've moved on,

37:53.020 --> 37:54.438
so you don't have to worry so much.

38:03.948 --> 38:06.200
What did you mean earlier when you said

38:07.493 --> 38:09.328
that people will start talking about me?

38:13.291 --> 38:14.959
I'm not the average man.

38:16.669 --> 38:19.380
"Who is the woman next to such a man?"

38:20.381 --> 38:21.882
"What's her story?"

38:23.175 --> 38:24.385
"Is she a single parent too?"

38:25.386 --> 38:26.721
People will speculate.

38:30.391 --> 38:32.268
You could become the subject of gossip.

38:37.273 --> 38:40.359
Is that why you turned down
my offer to be friends?

38:40.901 --> 38:41.902
You know...

38:43.446 --> 38:45.239
that's not why I did that.

38:49.618 --> 38:51.203
You said you moved on.

38:52.204 --> 38:53.497
We can be friends then.

38:59.962 --> 39:01.172
Why do you want...

39:03.007 --> 39:04.425
to be my friend?

39:06.469 --> 39:08.095
No reason.

39:10.973 --> 39:12.266
I don't need your pity.

39:15.144 --> 39:16.854
You have some sort
of weird victim mentality.

39:18.439 --> 39:20.024
You'd understand if you were in my shoes.

39:25.654 --> 39:27.656
Are you turning me down again then?

39:31.577 --> 39:32.995
Being friends isn't a big deal.

39:34.205 --> 39:35.664
We can ask each other how we're doing

39:37.166 --> 39:40.169
and meet from time to time if we want.

39:45.216 --> 39:46.759
What would your boyfriend say?

39:49.678 --> 39:53.265
Are you worried about me
or are you scared for yourself?

39:57.395 --> 39:59.522
This doesn't really need to be said,

40:01.399 --> 40:04.360
but I believe
that my life should be respected.

40:06.320 --> 40:10.324
From here on out,
I'd appreciate it if you didn't

40:12.076 --> 40:14.787
assume or worry about things
I don't mention.

40:18.374 --> 40:19.500
It makes me uncomfortable.

40:27.508 --> 40:28.759
Let's give it a shot.

40:31.387 --> 40:33.764
Let's be friends.

40:37.893 --> 40:39.687
Have you had a sudden change of heart?

40:42.148 --> 40:43.274
You're funny.

40:44.066 --> 40:45.526
Then you just gained a funny friend.

43:29.440 --> 43:30.733
It's your sister.

43:36.030 --> 43:37.197
What is she doing over there?

43:40.284 --> 43:41.827
Who is she with?

43:43.370 --> 43:44.622
It looks like Yeong-jae.

43:45.539 --> 43:46.540
Who?

43:47.750 --> 43:48.876
From that day?

43:57.509 --> 43:58.677
It is Yeong-jae.

44:01.096 --> 44:02.181
What's so funny?

44:02.723 --> 44:04.975
The fact that they're together.

44:05.601 --> 44:06.810
How is that funny?

44:11.023 --> 44:12.691
What's wrong with her?

44:14.693 --> 44:17.029
What's wrong?
They must've exchanged numbers.

44:17.696 --> 44:19.114
Unbelievable.

44:20.449 --> 44:21.617
Are you getting out?

44:28.290 --> 44:31.377
How do you expect to carry this on
if you think that's unbelievable?

44:31.460 --> 44:32.795
We're friends, so who cares?

44:36.632 --> 44:38.467
I usually choose my words wisely,

44:38.550 --> 44:40.761
but I don't know why I spurt things out
when I'm with you.

44:43.514 --> 44:45.349
Well, that made us become friends.

45:02.616 --> 45:03.742
You're home late.

45:09.164 --> 45:10.582
Hey, Jae-in.

45:12.501 --> 45:13.669
Where were you tonight?

45:13.836 --> 45:15.170
I saw everything, so be honest.

45:16.130 --> 45:17.005
Saw what?

45:17.089 --> 45:19.758
I saw you hanging out
with that future civil servant out front.

45:20.342 --> 45:21.385
Why didn't you say hi?

45:23.303 --> 45:24.555
Why were you with him?

45:25.389 --> 45:27.933
We're friends. We agreed to be friends.

45:28.517 --> 45:31.186
Someone your age shouldn't be his friend.

45:31.937 --> 45:34.565
Age and other aspects
don't matter with friendships.

45:35.983 --> 45:37.609
It's childish of you to think so.

45:48.620 --> 45:50.747
Jeong-in, about that pharmacist.

45:52.833 --> 45:54.543
- What about him?
- He seems decent.

45:56.003 --> 45:56.962
Why's that?

45:57.212 --> 45:59.131
Did someone say something?

45:59.256 --> 46:01.175
Yeong-jae talked about his friends,

46:01.258 --> 46:02.885
and the pharmacist seemed like the best.

46:03.969 --> 46:05.137
Should I make a move?

46:06.763 --> 46:07.764
Why not?

46:08.348 --> 46:10.684
One son-in-law is a doctor
and now a pharmacist can be added.

46:10.767 --> 46:12.186
Dad will be thrilled.

46:13.103 --> 46:14.313
Don't take it too far.

46:14.396 --> 46:16.607
Just remember
they're all connected to Gi-seok.

46:17.441 --> 46:18.942
That's your problem, not mine.

46:20.736 --> 46:21.987
Just think about it.

46:22.070 --> 46:24.072
It'll be an issue for you to date

46:24.156 --> 46:26.116
anyone from that group,

46:26.533 --> 46:27.659
but not me.

46:43.175 --> 46:44.426
Why are you following me out?

46:44.510 --> 46:47.262
Go back inside and readjust the budget.

46:47.346 --> 46:49.765
- Yes, sir.
- Mr. Kwon,

46:50.682 --> 46:52.851
is there an issue with the budget plan?

46:53.268 --> 46:57.272
You should've read the documents
before signing them

46:57.356 --> 46:59.358
and sending them up for my approval.

47:00.275 --> 47:03.445
Do you not care anymore
because you'll be leaving soon?

47:03.529 --> 47:05.989
No, of course not. I'd never be like that.

47:06.198 --> 47:08.575
- What happened is that--
- It's uncanny.

47:09.076 --> 47:11.787
The school operates in
a similar fashion every year,

47:11.870 --> 47:14.665
but the budget only increases
and never decreases.

47:15.999 --> 47:18.877
This is why they say
no one can be trusted in this world.

47:19.253 --> 47:22.714
I'm sorry, sir.
I'll be more thorough next time.

47:23.131 --> 47:25.008
You're always all talk.

47:25.342 --> 47:27.010
"I'll be more thorough next time."

47:27.970 --> 47:31.557
I loathe those who get by
on just their empty promises.

47:31.932 --> 47:33.225
I hear you, sir.

47:35.102 --> 47:37.062
That reminds me.

47:37.938 --> 47:40.857
How about we grab
that lunch you mentioned last time?

47:42.276 --> 47:44.820
I have plans with Assemblyman Jang.

47:44.903 --> 47:47.781
He's buying to celebrate
his daughter becoming a professor.

47:48.323 --> 47:49.366
I see.

47:50.742 --> 47:51.785
Enjoy, then.

48:45.631 --> 48:48.008
Gi-seok, yes. It's been a while.

48:49.885 --> 48:52.471
Of course. Why haven't you been in touch?

48:54.890 --> 48:56.683
We should if that's what you'd like.

48:57.351 --> 48:58.352
How about today?

49:00.145 --> 49:01.647
Where are you meeting my dad?

49:02.189 --> 49:04.524
Shouldn't you know what it's about
before getting riled up?

49:05.275 --> 49:06.818
It's probably about us getting married.

49:07.277 --> 49:08.403
And that annoys you?

49:09.321 --> 49:12.199
- That's not it.
- Of course it is.

49:14.368 --> 49:15.744
You're right. I'm pissed.

49:16.119 --> 49:17.954
I hate being pushed into it like this.

49:18.664 --> 49:20.666
You don't want to get married, do you?

49:24.419 --> 49:26.213
Is it marriage you hate, or just me?

49:29.758 --> 49:30.842
What is it?

49:36.181 --> 49:37.391
Why aren't you answering?

49:39.351 --> 49:40.394
Gi-seok.

49:42.562 --> 49:43.647
I'm listening.

49:44.898 --> 49:48.443
I think that we should
respect each other more.

49:50.862 --> 49:53.031
I don't want to get married just because

49:54.241 --> 49:55.742
we've been dating long enough.

49:57.994 --> 50:00.080
I'm sure that's how you feel too.

50:01.415 --> 50:02.666
Or maybe you don't.

50:05.168 --> 50:09.005
It's not like anything has changed
between us, so I guess--

50:09.172 --> 50:10.173
Hold on.

50:13.135 --> 50:14.469
You're acting strange.

50:16.972 --> 50:18.014
Something's different.

50:20.183 --> 50:21.226
Jeong-in.

50:21.852 --> 50:22.853
Yes?

50:23.395 --> 50:25.147
Is there something you're not telling me?

50:26.273 --> 50:27.274
No.

50:29.735 --> 50:30.902
Jeong-in.

50:32.070 --> 50:34.531
I'm sorry, but can we talk again later?

50:35.282 --> 50:37.951
Go home after work.
I'll call you on my way to you.

50:40.370 --> 50:41.496
What about my dad?

50:41.747 --> 50:43.915
I'll take care of that. See you later.

51:12.944 --> 51:15.447
Yes, Father. It's Gi-seok.

51:16.615 --> 51:18.492
I'm sorry about this,

51:18.992 --> 51:21.620
but a meeting came up for this evening.

51:22.454 --> 51:24.498
I'll have to take a rain check.

51:26.291 --> 51:27.417
That's right.

51:27.501 --> 51:29.836
- Take care.
- Bye.

51:33.006 --> 51:34.591
Don't you feel bad that his son is sick?

51:35.383 --> 51:37.385
More so because he's a man.

51:38.178 --> 51:39.179
Exactly.

51:41.515 --> 51:43.308
You should go home if you're that worried.

51:43.767 --> 51:46.353
He was discharged this morning
and is playing right now.

51:48.438 --> 51:50.273
It's a particularly slow day today.

51:52.442 --> 51:55.362
Isn't it a good thing
since it means less people are sick?

51:56.196 --> 51:58.365
If you open a pharmacy,
you'll go under in three months.

51:58.824 --> 52:00.325
I'm taking out the trash.

52:01.493 --> 52:03.286
How much will it cost to open one?

52:04.329 --> 52:06.373
It depends on where the location is.

52:06.915 --> 52:08.083
Are you considering it?

52:09.292 --> 52:11.503
I'm thinking
about moving back in with my parents.

52:15.882 --> 52:18.218
I'm a mother myself, but some might think

52:18.301 --> 52:20.345
that I'm not when they hear this.

52:21.012 --> 52:23.431
After my divorce, I asked my mom
to help out with the kids.

52:25.141 --> 52:26.601
To be honest, I regret it.

52:27.686 --> 52:29.604
The amount of help I received
was enormous,

52:29.729 --> 52:32.190
but I couldn't have a life.

52:33.733 --> 52:35.652
She was always watching the kids
and doing chores,

52:35.735 --> 52:38.530
so I thought I shouldn't do other things
and be with my kids.

52:39.322 --> 52:41.700
I wasn't even able to comfortably grab
a beer with my friends.

52:42.742 --> 52:44.244
Once you move back home,

52:44.703 --> 52:45.871
Yu Ji-ho will be gone.

52:46.246 --> 52:49.374
You'll only live as a son
and the father of your child.

52:53.295 --> 52:55.797
I want to tell you to be selfish.

52:56.923 --> 52:59.092
You have the right to live a happy life.

53:23.825 --> 53:25.118
Where's Jae-in?

53:26.286 --> 53:28.288
I don't know.
She wasn't here when I got home.

53:30.415 --> 53:32.334
- Can I get you anything?
- I'm good.

53:49.100 --> 53:50.226
Tell me then.

53:51.603 --> 53:52.812
What's the issue?

53:55.982 --> 53:57.484
I told you everything on the phone

53:58.568 --> 53:59.819
although it wasn't much.

54:02.030 --> 54:03.823
I'm glad you know.

54:17.712 --> 54:19.714
When the thought of marriage suddenly...

54:21.299 --> 54:22.634
becomes a reality,

54:24.469 --> 54:25.553
they say...

54:27.597 --> 54:29.224
most get cold feet...

54:31.351 --> 54:32.894
and rethink the idea as a whole.

54:36.731 --> 54:38.483
But your reaction is more than that.

54:41.861 --> 54:43.071
Am I wrong?

54:47.742 --> 54:49.077
I don't know.

54:51.830 --> 54:54.207
What exactly do you mean by that?

54:55.625 --> 54:58.211
You're usually smart
and know what you want.

54:58.294 --> 55:00.338
Why have you become
so vague all of a sudden?

55:03.717 --> 55:04.801
Beats me.

55:06.761 --> 55:08.763
Something must have triggered this.

55:09.889 --> 55:10.849
No?

55:11.891 --> 55:15.395
Only that can explain this
and help me understand.

55:21.026 --> 55:21.943
Gi-seok,

55:28.074 --> 55:29.451
I think we need a break.

55:35.915 --> 55:37.083
Are you breaking up with me?

55:49.137 --> 55:51.056
We'll end up married anyway, right?

55:54.392 --> 55:56.770
- My family hasn't--
- If marriage was my only goal,

55:58.271 --> 55:59.814
I wouldn't have stayed with you.

56:18.666 --> 56:19.959
Is time the only thing you need?

56:25.048 --> 56:28.468
Are you sure that
there's nothing else going on?

56:32.180 --> 56:33.431
I'm sure.

56:39.771 --> 56:41.147
Fine. I'll give you space then.

56:51.658 --> 56:52.700
Are you leaving?

56:54.828 --> 56:55.995
You'd prefer that.

56:57.705 --> 56:58.915
That's cruel to hear.

57:07.757 --> 57:10.510
Get some rest
and reduce some of the anxiety.

57:22.939 --> 57:24.899
I want to go to the zoo.

57:25.650 --> 57:28.736
It's still too cold,
so there won't be many animals outside.

57:29.988 --> 57:31.948
Dinosaurs don't get cold.

57:32.991 --> 57:34.409
They actually do.

57:41.875 --> 57:42.917
Let me grab that for you.

57:46.796 --> 57:49.132
Don't. I can do it myself.

57:52.760 --> 57:55.597
All right. I'll be right over there,

57:56.055 --> 57:58.057
so don't push up too high. Got it?

58:01.311 --> 58:02.520
I'll be behind you.

58:20.580 --> 58:23.124
LEE JEONG-IN

58:23.208 --> 58:24.292
How have things been?

58:49.234 --> 58:52.070
Good. How have you been?

58:53.154 --> 58:55.907
It's probably your day off.
I'm actually at work today.

59:16.594 --> 59:18.930
Can I ask what you do for a living?

59:31.192 --> 59:34.445
Jeong-in, can you take a look
at my header for the library?

59:34.529 --> 59:36.197
We both know you did a good job.

59:39.117 --> 59:40.118
Hey.

59:40.702 --> 59:43.371
Weren't you and Gi-seok on a break?
Are you back together?

59:44.414 --> 59:45.331
It's not him.

59:45.415 --> 59:48.418
Then that's more suspicious
considering the smile on your face.

59:49.877 --> 59:52.255
- Aren't you busy?
- I am.

59:54.841 --> 59:55.717
Darn.

01:00:13.526 --> 01:00:16.112
Are we really off to see dinosaurs?

01:00:17.488 --> 01:00:18.531
Yes, we are.

01:00:20.408 --> 01:00:23.578
But you said that
the dinosaurs were too cold to come out.

01:00:25.038 --> 01:00:27.290
They're not at the zoo but somewhere else.

01:00:28.791 --> 01:00:29.792
Where?

01:00:32.211 --> 01:00:33.296
Someplace warm.

01:00:47.852 --> 01:00:49.687
ARCHIVE
RESTRICTED AREA

01:01:16.255 --> 01:01:18.716
WERE THERE DINOSAURS THAT LIKED FLOWERS?

01:02:40.923 --> 01:02:42.008
My gosh!

01:02:47.972 --> 01:02:49.223
I know who you are.

01:02:51.517 --> 01:02:52.477
You're Eun-u, right?

01:02:53.060 --> 01:02:54.604
How do you know me?

01:02:56.647 --> 01:02:57.774
How do I know you?

01:02:58.691 --> 01:02:59.525
Take a guess.

01:03:00.485 --> 01:03:01.861
Dad, who is she?

01:03:03.196 --> 01:03:04.489
Who do you think I am?

01:03:05.031 --> 01:03:05.865
Go ahead and guess.

01:03:11.078 --> 01:03:12.163
Mom?

01:03:56.082 --> 01:03:57.291
I knew something was up.

01:03:57.500 --> 01:03:59.961
- We agreed to be friends.
- Because that's all you could be?

01:04:00.044 --> 01:04:01.796
No physical response means

01:04:01.879 --> 01:04:04.006
that there are no feelings left.

01:04:04.090 --> 01:04:05.508
Think of the opposite though.

01:04:05.591 --> 01:04:07.134
The response will be involuntary.

01:04:07.218 --> 01:04:08.970
- Are you getting married?
- Soon.

01:04:09.053 --> 01:04:10.221
We've been dating for a while.

01:04:10.304 --> 01:04:11.597
Ji-ho has a kid.

01:04:11.681 --> 01:04:13.307
He met the mom at a young age,

01:04:13.391 --> 01:04:15.101
but she left after having the baby.

01:04:15.601 --> 01:04:16.769
He should've done better.

01:04:17.270 --> 01:04:18.563
Would that have changed things?

01:04:18.646 --> 01:04:20.648
Doing better or not isn't the issue here.

01:04:20.731 --> 01:04:22.024
Feelings have changed.

01:04:22.108 --> 01:04:24.610
Are we at a point where
we need to work on our relationship?

01:04:24.694 --> 01:04:25.945
Is there someone else?

01:04:26.028 --> 01:04:27.446
I'm actually not sure.

01:04:27.530 --> 01:04:30.741
I don't know what's okay and
what is considered as "crossing the line."

01:04:30.825 --> 01:04:32.201
That's why this is frustrating.

01:04:32.285 --> 01:04:33.703
I ended it before I get crazier.

01:04:33.786 --> 01:04:36.330
Because I know how tough
things will get for her.

01:04:39.208 --> 01:04:41.252
Subtitle translation by Hye-lim Park
